<subSubSection id="C35C48E8FFAFFFD3F4CCFEB1FDA9A3A0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFEB1FDA9A3A0" blockId="2.[136,1451,381,444]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
Following the transfer of two of the six species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F6FEFEB1FBC5A383" authority="(Mueller 1853: 368) Schulz (1924: 177)" authorityName="Schulz" authorityPageNumber="177" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityPageNumber="368" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[698,1037,381,408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F6FEFEB1FCFAA38C" box="[698,818,381,407]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Arabidella</emphasis>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD76692FFAFFFD3F73AFEB1FBC5A383" author="Shaw, E. A." box="[894,1037,381,408]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" pagination="145 - 253" refId="ref3744" refString="Shaw, E. A. (1965) Taxonomic revision of some Australian endemic genera of Cruciferae. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia 89: 145 - 253." type="journal article" year="1965">Shaw (1965)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F075FEB1FB64A38C" authorityName="Schulz" authorityYear="1924" box="[1073,1196,381,407]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F075FEB1FB64A38C" box="[1073,1196,381,407]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Lemphoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the remaining species can be distinguished by the following key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C48E8FFAFFFD3F4CCFE2AFA63A090" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="key">
<key id="FFD74C52FFAFFFD3F4CCFE2AFA63A090" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCFE2AFBCAA002" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFE2AFA63A3E0" blockId="2.[136,1451,486,652]" box="[136,1451,486,508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFE2AFA63A3E0" box="[136,1451,486,508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
1a. Annual herbs with basal leaf rosette at least during flowering; stems without bark ...................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F16CFE2AFA63A3E0" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1965" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1320,1451,486,507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nasturtium">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F16CFE2AFA63A3E0" box="[1320,1451,486,507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">A. nasturtium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFDCFFBCAA002" blockId="2.[136,1451,486,652]" box="[136,1026,515,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFDCFFBCAA002" box="[136,1026,515,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">1b. Woody shrubs or subshrubs without basal leaf rosette; stems usually with some bark.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCFDECFBC0A049" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFDECFA63A02F" blockId="2.[136,1451,486,652]" box="[136,1451,543,565]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFDECFA63A02F" box="[136,1451,543,565]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
2a. Fruiting pedicel divaricate to horizontal or slightly recurved; all leaves undivided, rarely some 2- or 3-sect ................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F10DFDECFA63A02F" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1965" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1353,1451,543,565]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filifolia">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F10DFDECFA63A02F" box="[1353,1451,543,565]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">A. filifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFDF0FBC0A049" blockId="2.[136,1451,486,652]" box="[136,1032,572,594]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFDF0FBC0A049" box="[136,1032,572,594]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">2b. Fruiting pedicels suberect to ascending, straight; almost all leaves 2-, 3-, or multisect.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCFD95FA63A090" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFD95FA63A075" blockId="2.[136,1451,486,652]" box="[136,1451,601,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFD95FA63A075" box="[136,1451,601,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
3a. Stems glabrous; flowers in corymb; fruit 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F61AFD95FD77A074" box="[606,703,601,623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.0">1–2.5 mm</quantity>
wide; gynophore (0.8–) 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F7ECFD95FBC0A074" box="[936,1032,601,623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.0">1–2.2 mm</quantity>
long..................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F158FD95FA63A075" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1965" box="[1308,1451,601,622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaucescens">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F158FD95FA63A075" box="[1308,1451,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">A. glaucescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFDBAFA63A090" blockId="2.[136,1451,486,652]" box="[136,1451,630,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFDBAFA63A090" box="[136,1451,630,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
3b. Stems often papillate; flowers in lax raceme; fruit 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F6F1FDBAFCE0A090" box="[693,808,630,652]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide; gynophore 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F792FDBAFB81A090" box="[982,1097,630,652]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.5 mm</quantity>
long ................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F10CFDBAFA63A090" authorityName="Schulz" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1352,1451,630,651]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trisecta">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F10CFDBAFA63A090" box="[1352,1451,630,651]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">A. trisecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
